       "We are sending a strong message to you now, that you have declared war against the police. You can run, but you can't hide. We are going to fight without any fear," said Mathebula.            "Sergeant Monana was killed at Gamotibidi Trust on 5 March. He was off duty at the time and was travelling with a female friend. The two were accosted by four armed suspects who acted like they needed to talk.     Anyone who may have information on the whereabouts of the suspects can contact Detective Warrant Officer Mduduzi Aubrey Motubatsi on 072 320 3194 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111 or alternatively send information via the MYSAPS app.